In 1980, after Italian arms manufacturer Beretta had completed its contracts to produce firearms for Brazil's military, Taurus purchased Beretta's Sao Paulo manufacturing plant along with the tooling, technical drawings, and work force necessary to produce several different pistol designs. title: For Sale:  M+M M10 AK47
postcontent: You wouldn't tell it's an AK. I've got so many people asking me, is it an ACR?So the base gun is a M10 which is a Romanian AK. Hold your breathe there, it's not the normal Romanian WASR that imported by CAI can compare of. M+M has imported brand new gun from their Arsenal (other than assembled with some "Part kit" as century does), and then CNC cut the magwell here in the US. It has 16" Cold Hammer Forged barrel Made in Romania, all other parts are also brand new mil spec Rom made, only with some quality US substitute parts to make it 922r compliant, such as Tapco G2 trigger, etc. So you can use either imported or US made magazine.CAI sued M+M for they are making better rifle (well, the excuse is they accuse them break the monopoly contract), and these M10 are the most accurate AKs I've ever seen. I do precision shooting, and a good way to exam a rifle is shooting 5 groups of 5 shot each. You can get lucky shot for 1 group of 3 shots, but 5x5 don't cheat. and that's the method many professional firearm reviewers use. Shooting @ 100 yard with a 3-9x scope, I can get 5x5 test average of 1.5 moa (which is impressive for an AK) out of Brown Bear HP ammo.Upgrade has been done, including: M10                                                                                                                                 - 699.99 (when I purchased and hard to find now.)whole gun FDE ceracoat,                                                                                                   - 350Kerbs enhanced bolt hold open safety lever,                                                                    - 60M+M enhanced mag release with CAA extended ambi mag release lever,    - 60Ultimak gas tube with picatinny rails,                                                                                  - 98ALL FDE Magpul furniture: Zhukov hand guard and Zhukov-S Stock, hogue grip,                                                                                                                                               - 220Latest Gen AK Compact Muzzle brake from CNC Warrior, same as those used by Russian Spec Ops.                                                                                                             - 60Shock absorber installed.                                                                                                   - 10GripPOD G.P.S. 02 foregrip / Bipod combo. the real US military stuff, not Chinese knock offs.                                                                                                                  - 100I will include 2 to 4 steel AK mags into this package.So you can do the maths, I spent well over 1600 on this gun. Like the HK416, the MR556A1 is a major product improvement over conventional AR-type carbines and rifles. The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating "pusher" rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers. The MR556A1 uses the HK proprietary gas piston operating system, employing a piston and a solid operating "pusher" rod in place of the gas tube normally found in AR15/M16/M4-style firearms. This method of operation virtually eliminates malfunctions that are common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. This is the same key feature critical to the success of the HK416 rifles used by leading military and law enforcement customers. The MR556A1 is produced in the USA using American and German made components. The MR556A1 uses many of the same assemblies and accessories originally developed for the HK416 including the HK free-floating four-quadrant rail system. The HK Free Floating Rail System (FFRS) handguard has four MIL-STD-1913 "Picatinny" rails and allows all current accessories, sights, lights, and aimers used on M4/M16-type arms to be fitted to the MR series. The HK rail system can be installed and removed with simple tools and returns to zero reinstalled. The MR556A1 also has a Picatinny rail machined into the top of its upper receiver for mounting optics and mechanical sights. Unlike earlier prototypes, major subassemblies, including the MR556A1 upper receiver/barrel assembly. are fully interchangeable with other high quality AR-style firearms. MR556A1 upper receiver kits can be used to retrofit competing legacy AR systems. Like the famous HK416, the MR556A1 uses a German-made barrel produced by Heckler & Koch's famous cold hammer forging process. The highest quality steel is used in this unqiue manufacturing process producing a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life. But unlike the HK416, the MR556A1 does not use a chrome-lined barrel. Chrome-lining can sometimes mask bore imperfections and negatively affect accuracy. For the new series of Heckler & Koch semi-automatic MR rifles, HK designers and engineers belive best accuracy comes with an unlined bore. Used with the HK Free Floating Rail System, the barrel does not touch the handguard, ensuring the barrel is truly free-floating for maximum accuracy. The unchromed barrel has an internal profile of 6 lands and grooves with a 1 in 7 inch (178mm) twist. It is also moderately "swagged" with a slightly smaller internal diameter at the muzzle end than the chamber end. This feature has a positive effect on bullet accuracy and velocity. The thick, heavy contour 16.5" MR556A1 barrel also contributes to its excellent accuracy. A precise enhanced two-stage trigger adds significantly to the accuracy of the M556A1 and an extended latch charging handle makes operating the rifle with a telescopic sight easier. The retractable buttstock can be locked into a solid, non-moving position by tightening an Allen screw in the bottom of the stock. Special target rifle takedown pins ensure the upper and lower receivers are firmly mated for accurate performance. Designed to function with a wide variety of high quality 5.56x45mm ammunition, the MR556A1 uses a C.I.P. dimensionedchamber (a chamber with dimensions specified by the Commision Internationale Permanete). The MR556A1 also functions reliably with most quality Caliber .223 Remington ammunition. The MR556A1 is being produced with the same commitment to quality as German-made HK firearms. By using joint U.S./German manufacturing, Heckler & Koch leverages the relative strengths of two continents to make the preemient AR-type firearm, combining the designs innovations of the USA and Germany into one new porduct. Technology: Highest Quality Steel:  They use the same grade steel used in making cannon barrels - for its rifle barrels. Using the famous HK cold hammer forging process, this advanced technology manufacturing produces a barrel that provides superior accuracy and long service life. It is also moderately "swagged" with a slightly smaller internal diameter at the muzzle end than the chamber end. This has a positive effect on bullet accuracy and velocity and the thick, heavy contour MR series barrels also contributes to its precision.
